o the city pool, where a chance to be with his crush, Bridget Fitzsimmons, little sister of his bully Jimmy, eventually leads to an embarrassing [[erection]] incident. Frank receives two promotions at work, one of which was his old position and his friend Rosie was next in line for, making the latter utterly upset and prompting Frank to try and mend fences between him and his boss, Bob Pogo.\n |LineColor       = #A69580\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 20\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n |Title           = Mr. Murphy's Wild Ride\n |DirectedBy      = Sylvain Lavoie\n |WrittenBy       = Michael Price\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|30}}\n |ProdCode        = 304\n |ShortSummary    = Frank, Chet, Vic, and the rest of the husband neighbors begin to work on the baby's new room and soon, Chet takes Frank on a joyride in a jet while Bill and Phillip's friendship is put to the test when the latter gets jealous of Bill's crush on Bridget.\n |LineColor       = #A69580\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 21\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n |Title           = Battle of the Sexes\n |DirectedBy      = Olivier Schramm\n |WrittenBy       = Emily Towers\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|30}}\n |ProdCode        = 305\n |ShortSummary    = Sue hosts another depressing focus group for her invention. Frank is scared Chet might want to hang out with Vic. Bill and Bridget sneak out after dark and wander around the town as a 'first date'. Sue discovers that Chet treats Nguyen-Nguyen very abusively.\n |LineColor       = #A69580\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 22\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n |Title           = Punch Drunk\n |DirectedBy      = Sylvain Lavoie\n |WrittenBy       = Joe Heslinga\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|11|30}}\n |ProdCode        = 306\n |ShortSummary    = Sue tries to warn Frank after discovering Chet treats Nguyen-Nguyen horribly, which puts the latter in an awkward position at a 4th of July neighborhood barbecue.\n |LineColor       = #A69580\n}}