{"title_page": "Texel", "text_new": "{{about|the Dutch island|other uses|}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}}\n{{Refimprove|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n<!-- Name and transliteration -->\n| name                    = Texel\n| settlement_type         = [[List of municipalities of the Netherlands|Municipality]] and [[island]]\n<!-- Images, nickname, motto -->\n| image_skyline           = Texel island.jpg\n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = North end of the island with the [[Eierland Lighthouse]] in 2015\n| image_flag              = Texel flag.svg\n| flag_size               = 100x80px\n| flag_alt                = \n| image_shield            = Texel wapen.svg\n| shield_size             = 100x80px\n| shield_alt              = \n<!-- Maps, coordinates -->\n| image_map               = Map - NL - Municipality code 0448 (2009).svg\n| map_alt                 = Highlighted position of Texel in a municipal map of North Holland\n| map_caption             = Location in North Holland\n| coordinates             = {{coord|53|3|N|4|48|E|region:NL-NH|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes   = \n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[Netherlands]]\n| subdivision_type1       = Province\n| subdivision_name1       = [[North Holland]]\n| government_footnotes    = <ref name=\"mayor_now\">{{cite web\n |url         = http://www.texel.nl/de-gemeente/bw-samenstelling-en-portefeuilles_42167/\n |title       = B&W samenstelling en portefeuilles\n |trans-title = Mayor and aldermen members and tasks\n |language    = Dutch\n |publisher   = Gemeente Texel\n |accessdate  = 22 March 2014\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20140727100539/http://www.texel.nl/de-gemeente/bw-samenstelling-en-portefeuilles_42167/\n |archivedate = 27 July 2014\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref>\n| governing_body          = [[Municipal council (Netherlands)|Municipal council]]\n| leader_party            = [[Democrats 66|D66]]\n| leader_title            = [[Burgemeester|Mayor]]\n| leader_name             = Michiel Uitdehaag\n<!-- Geographic information -->\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n<!-- ALL fields with measurements have automatic unit conversion -->\n<!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| area_footnotes          = <ref>{{Dutch municipality total area|dataref}}</ref>\n<!-- square kilometers -->\n| area_total_km2          = {{Dutch municipality total area|Texel}}\n| area_land_km2           = {{Dutch municipality land area|Texel}}\n| area_water_km2          = {{Dutch municipality water area|Texel}}\n| elevation_footnotes     = <ref name=\"AHN\">{{cite web \n |url = http://www.ahn.nl/postcodetool\n |title = Postcodetool for 1791AT\n |trans-title = \n |language = Dutch\n |author = <!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> \n |date = \n |work = Actueel Hoogtebestand Nederland\n |publisher = Het Waterschapshuis\n |accessdate = 22 March 2014}}</ref>\n| elevation_m             = 2\n| elevation_max_footnotes = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| elevation_max_m         =\n| elevation_min_footnotes = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| elevation_min_m         =\n<!-- Population, demographics -->\n| population_footnotes    = <ref>{{Dutch municipality population|dataref}}</ref>\n| population_total        = {{Dutch municipality population|Texel}}\n| population_as_of        = {{MONTHNAME|{{Dutch municipality population|popbasemonth}}}} {{Dutch municipality population|popbaseyear}}\n| population_density_km2  = {{Dutch municipality population density|Texel}} <!-- For automatic calculation: auto-->\n| population_demonym      = Tesselaar, Texelaar\n<!-- Other information -->\n| timezone                = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset              = +1\n| timezone_DST            = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST          = +2\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal codes in the Netherlands|Postcode]]\n| postal_code             = 1790\u20131797\n| area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in the Netherlands|Area code]]\n| area_code               = 0222\n| website                 = {{URL|1=http://www.texel.nl}}\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n\n'''Texel''' ({{IPA-nl|\u02c8t\u025bs\u0259l|-|422 Texel.ogg}}) is a [[municipality]] and an [[island]] with a population of 13,643 in the province of [[North Holland]] in the [[Netherlands]]. It is the largest and most populated island of the [[West Frisian Islands]] in the [[Wadden Sea]]. The island is situated north of [[Den Helder]], northeast of [[Noorderhaaks]], also known as \"Razende Bol\" and southwest of [[Vlieland]].\n\n== Name ==\nThe name ''Texel'' is Frisian, but because of [[Dutch language#Classification|historical sound-changes in Dutch]], where all -x- sounds have been replaced with -s- sounds (compare for instance English ''fox'', Frisian ''fokse'', German ''Fuchs'' with Dutch ''vos''), the name is typically pronounced ''Tessel'' in Dutch.<ref>{{cite book|last=Donaldson|first=Bruce C.|year=1983|title=Dutch: A Linguistic History of Holland and Belgium|publisher=Martinus Nijhoff|place=Leiden||isbn=9789024791668|page=151}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe [[All Saints' Flood (1170)]] created the islands of Texel and [[Wieringen]] from [[North Holland]].<ref name=\"ley196110\">{{Cite magazine\n |last=Ley\n |first=Willy\n |author=\n |last2=\n |first2=\n |date=October 1961\n |title=The Home-Made Land\n |department=For Your Information\n |url=https://archive.org/stream/Galaxy_v19n06_1961-08#page/n65/mode/1up\n |magazine=Galaxy Science Fiction\n |pages=92-106\n |type=\n}}</ref> In the 13th century [[Ada, Countess of Holland]] was held prisoner on Texel by her uncle William.\n\nTexel received [[City rights in the Netherlands|city rights]] in 1415.\n\nTexel was involved in the [[Battle of Scheveningen]] (1653) during the [[First Anglo-Dutch War]] and the [[Battle of Texel]] (1673) during the [[Third Anglo-Dutch War]].\n[[File:Dutch ships in the roadstead of Texel (the 'Gouden Leeuw' of Cornelis Tromp in the center)(Ludolf Backhuysen, 1671).jpg|thumb|left|Dutch ships in the [[roadstead]] of Texel, 1671]]\n[[File:The wreck of HMS Hero in the Texel, 25 December 1811.jpg|thumb|left|HMS ''Hero'' wrecked at Haak Sands near Texel December 25, 1811]]\nTexel is also famous in military history as the only place where a navy was defeated on horseback. Occupying Holland in January 1795, the French continental army learned that the Dutch navy had been frozen into the ice around Texel, so Commandant [[Louis Joseph Lahure]] and 128 men rode up to it and demanded surrender. No shots were fired.\n\n[[HMS Lutine]], a [[United Kingdom|British]] frigate loaded with British [[gold]], sank along the Texel coast in a storm during 1799.  Her wreck shifted in the sands; despite several  intensive, well financed  searches, only a few treasures have been found.    <ref>https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/mystery-of-the-sinking-of-hms-lutine-f0279pwqn</ref> A beaker made from a silver bar is displayed in the [[National Maritime Museum]] at  Greenwich. Her bell was recovered and is now in the headquarters of [[Lloyds of London]], where it is tolled before announcing important news.<ref>https://medium.com/markelmarine/the-story-of-the-lutine-bell-ceb3e9c03e09</ref> \n\nIn 1797, Texel was involved in the [[Battle of Camperdown]] during the [[French Revolutionary Wars]].\n\nDuring the [[American Revolution]], Texel was used as a haven port for the [[USS Bonhomme Richard (1765)|USS ''Bonhomme Richard'']] before it sank off the coast of [[Flamborough Head]] in Britain in September 1779. In that final action, [[John Paul Jones]] defeated and captured the British ship [[HMS Serapis (1779)|HMS ''Serapis'']], which he sailed to Texel for desperately needed repairs. This event further complicated Anglo-Dutch relations.\n\nDuring the [[First World War]] in 1914, the [[Battle off Texel]] took place off the coast of Texel.\n\nOn the night of 31 August 1940, the sea to the northwest of Texel was the scene of the sinking of two British destroyers and the severe damage of a third by German mines in what is known as the [[Texel Disaster]].\n\nAt the end of [[Second World War]] in 1945, the [[Georgian uprising on Texel]] took place on the island.\n\n==Geography ==\n[[File:Texel-natuur-OpenTopo.jpg|thumb|upright|''2014 map of Texel'']]\n\nThe municipality is located at {{coord|53|3|N|4|48|E}} north of the mainland of the province of [[North Holland]] and west of the mainland of the province of [[Friesland]]. The island of Texel is situated north of the city of [[Den Helder]], northeast of the uninhabited island of [[Noorderhaaks]], which is part of the municipality, and southwest of the island of [[Vlieland]].\n\nThe island includes the seven villages:\n{{columns-list|colwidth=12em|\n* [[De Cocksdorp]]\n* [[De Koog]]\n* [[De Waal]]\n* [[Den Burg]]\n* [[Den Hoorn, North Holland|Den Hoorn]]\n* [[Oosterend]]\n* [[Oudeschild]]\n}} and the small townships of \n{{columns-list|colwidth=12em|\n* Bargen\n* De Nes\n* Dijkmanshuizen\n* [[Driehuizen, Texel|Driehuizen]]\n* Harkebuurt\n* 't Horntje\n* Midden-Eierland\n* Molenbuurt\n* Nieuweschild\n* Noorderbuurt\n* Ongeren\n* Oost\n* Spang\n* Spijkdorp\n* Tienhoven\n* Westermient\n* Zevenhuizen\n* Zuid-Eierland\n}}\nThe island of Texel was originally made up of two islands, Texel proper to the south and [[Eierland]] to the northeast, which were connected by [[shoal]]s. In the early seventeenth century, the islands were connected by a [[Levee|dyke]] to keep the [[North Sea]] from ravaging the coastal areas of Texel proper. In the mid-nineteenth century a [[polder]] completed the northern half of the island. Today, Texel forms the largest natural barrier between the North Sea and the [[Wadden Sea]].\n\nThe dune landscape along the western coast of the island is protected as [[Dunes of Texel National Park]].\n\n=== Landscape ===\nThe dune landscape on Texel is a unique habitat for wildlife. Notable areas include [[Dunes_of_Texel_National_Park#De_Slufter|De Slufter]], where the tide comes in and meets the dunes, forming a marshy environment rich in both fauna and flora. Texel is known for its wildlife, particularly in winter, when [[bird of prey|birds of prey]] and [[goose|geese]] take up residence. About one third of Texel is a protected nature reserve. A wetland called Utopia has been designed for birds to nest in.<ref>[https://www.natuurmonumenten.nl/nieuws/utopia-voor-vogels Utopia voor vogels]</ref>\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery mode=packed>\nFile:Slufter2.jpg|The [[Dunes of Texel National Park]]\nFile:Texel Landscape.jpg|Texel Landscape\nFile:De Koog - Koogerstrand - View NorthWest.jpg|De Koog - Koogerstrand - View Northwest\nFile:Dunes on Texel.jpg|Dunes on Texel\nFile:Beach_Texel_Netherlands.jpg|Beach on the island of Texel\nFile:Duinen van Texel5.jpg|Duinen van Texel\nFile:Ecomare - De Slufter 2014 (slufter-excursie2014-6495-sw).jpg|Nature and environment excursion in De Slufter\nFile:Nederland - Texel - panoramio.jpg|Texel\n</gallery>\n\n===Climate===\n{{Weather box\n|location = Texel\n|metric first = Yes\n|single line = Yes\n| Jan record high C = 13.7\n| Feb record high C = 14.9\n| Mar record high C = 20.5\n| Apr record high C = 27.9\n| May record high C = 31.0\n| Jun record high C = 31.7\n| Jul record high C = 34.6\n| Aug record high C = 33.8\n| Sep record high C = 32.6\n| Oct record high C = 24.8\n| Nov record high C = 17.7\n| Dec record high C = 15.3\n|year record high C = \n|Jan high C = 5.5\n|Feb high C = 5.5\n|Mar high C = 8.3\n|Apr high C = 11.7\n|May high C = 15.4\n|Jun high C = 18\n|Jul high C = 20.3\n|Aug high C = 20.6\n|Sep high C = 17.9\n|Oct high C = 14\n|Nov high C = 9.7\n|Dec high C = 6.4\n|Jan low C = 1.2\n|Feb low C = 0.8\n|Mar low C = 2.8\n|Apr low C = 5\n|May low C = 8.6\n|Jun low C = 11.3\n|Jul low C = 13.8\n|Aug low C = 14\n|Sep low C = 11.7\n|Oct low